ng reflects wider Hampshire demand patterns, with village stock often commanding premiums when supply is limited.","asOf":"2026-05","sourceUrl":"https://www.rightmove.co.uk/house-prices/SO21.html"},"thingsToDo":["Countryside walking/cycling on local rights of way","Visit nearby market-town amenities, pubs and heritage attractions"],"placesToEat":["Country pubs and cafés in the surrounding village/town catchment"],"pros":["Attractive rural setting with community identity","Access to larger towns without living in dense urban areas"],"cons":["Amenity choice is smaller than in major towns","Most households rely on car travel for many trips"],"whoItSuits":"Well suited to buyers seeking rural or semi-rural Hampshire living with realistic expectations about car dependency and travel to larger service centres.","broadbandMedianMbps":null,"nearestStation":null,"primarySupermarket":null,"images":[],"sources":[{"label":"Wikipedia — Colden Common","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Colden_Common"},{"label":"Hampshire County Council — Find a school","url":"https://www.hants.gov.uk/educationandlearning/findaschool"},{"label":"Rightmove House Prices SO21","url":"https://www.rightmove.co.uk/house-prices/SO21.html"},{"label":"National Rail stations and journey info","url":"https://www.nationalrail.co.uk/"}]},{"id":"colemore-gu32","name":"Colemore","village":"","town":"Petersfield","county":"Hampshire","postcode":"GU32","hubCity":"","regionDir":"","settlementType":"","subRegion":"","coords":{"lat":51.07444,"lng":-0.97852},"coordsSource":"unset","houseTypeIds":[],"status":"researched","overview":"A village and former civil parish — now part of the merged Colemore and Priors Dean parish — in the East Hampshire district. Colemore sits in the Hampshire Downs about five miles north-west of Petersfield, off lanes north of the A272. It was once a sizeable medieval settlement; the site of the abandoned village south-west of the church and south-east of Manor Farm is a scheduled ancient monument (Historic England 1001805), with the church of St Peter ad Vincula the only substantial medieval survival. The church is now redundant, vested in the Churches Conservation Trust, and notable for its 12th-century Norman chancel arch. Today Colemore is a scatter of farmhouses, the church, Manor Farmhouse (Grade II listed) and a handful of cottages — much of the parish land is tied to the Rotherfield Park estate. The Pub With No Name (The White Horse) at neighbouring Priors Dean serves the wider parish.","character":"Deserted-medieval-village landscape — wide skies, sheep pasture, ancient hedgerows, one redundant Norman church. Estate-tied and very quiet. Stock is dominated by listed farmhouses and a few converted barns.","amenities":["Church of St Peter ad Vincula (Grade II* listed, Churches Conservation Trust)","Manor Farmhouse (Grade II listed)","Scheduled ancient monument: deserted medieval village (HE 1001805)","(at Priors Dean ~0.8 mi:) The Pub With No Name (White Horse Inn)","Footpaths to Newton Valence, East Tisted and Hawkley"],"schools":[{"name":"Froxfield Church of England Primary and Pre-School","phase":"Primary","ofsted":"Good (March 2024)","distance":"2.5 mi","url":"https://reports.ofsted.gov.uk/provider/21/116289"},{"name":"Ropley Church of England Primary School","phase":"Primary","ofsted":"Good","distance":"3.0 mi","url":"https://www.ropley.hants.sch.uk/"},{"name":"The Petersfield School","phase":"Secondary","ofsted":"Good","distance":"5.0 mi","url":"https://www.tps.hants.sch.uk/"}],"transport":{"nearestStation":"Alton (5.5 mi)","commutes":[{"to":"London Waterloo","time":"1h 6m – 1h 18m direct","mode":"drive to Alton + direct South Western Railway","source":"https://www.thetrainline.com/train-times/alton-to-london-waterloo"},{"to":"London Waterloo (alt.)","time":"1h 2m – 1h 17m direct","mode":"drive to Petersfield + direct South Western Railway","source":"https://www.southwesternrailway.com/train-times/petersfield-to-london-waterloo"}],"roads":"A272 (Petersfield–Winchester) ~2 mi south; A32 (Alton–Fareham) ~3 mi west; A3 (London–Portsmouth) ~6 mi east at Petersfield"},"prices":{"avgSold12Mo":null,"avgDetached":null,"avgSemi":null,"avgTerraced":null,"avgFlat":null,"source":"https://www.rightmove.co.uk/house-prices/gu32.html","asOf":"2026-05"},"thingsToDo":["Church of St Peter ad Vincula (open in season via Churches Conservation Trust)","Hangers Way walking through Hawkley and Selborne","Selborne and Gilbert White''s House (~3.5 mi)","Rotherfield Park public open days (National Garden Scheme)","Cycling on quiet lanes around Priors Dean and Newton Valence"],"placesToEat":[{"name":"The Pub With No Name (White Horse)","type":"Country pub with rooms","notes":"17th-century pub at Priors Dean ~0.8 mi, reopened 2023; cask ales, dining room with inglenook","url":"https://www.thepubwithnoname.uk/"},{"name":"The Trooper Inn","type":"Pub with rooms","notes":"17th-century inn at High Cross, ~3 mi south-east","url":"https://www.trooperinn.com/"}],"pros":["Scheduled-ancient-monument landscape — deeply historic with very low building density","Among the lowest council tax precepts in East Hants (Colemore & Priors Dean parish Band D £1,982.51 in 2026/27 — below most neighbours)","Two heritage-quality pubs within 3 miles (Pub With No Name, The Trooper)","Within easy drive of both Alton and Petersfield stations","Strong landscape protection — most of the parish is in the South Downs National Park"],"cons":["Functionally a working farming hamlet — no shop, no school, no active church for services","Open-market stock is dominated by listed farmhouses or estate-tied properties; freehold turnover is very thin","No public transport to count on","Properties on listed-building consent — alterations need careful planning","Rural broadband: speeds vary sharply by individual postcode"],"whoItSuits":"Buyers wanting a Grade II listed farmhouse or converted barn in a scheduled deserted-medieval-village landscape, with two heritage pubs nearby and good A272/A32 access. Strong fit for retirees, country-house buyers, and home-workers happy to drive five miles for the station. Not for first-time buyers or those needing village amenities on foot.","nearestStation":"Alton (5.5 mi)","primarySupermarket":"Sainsbury''s Alton, Sainsbury Way (~5.5 mi); Waitrose Petersfield (~6 mi)","images":[],"sources":[{"label":"Wikipedia — Colemore","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Colemore"},{"label":"Wikipedia — Priors Dean","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Priors_Dean"},{"label":"Historic England — Deserted medieval village at Colemore","url":"https://historicengland.org.uk/listing/the-list/list-entry/1001805"},{"label":"Churches Conservation Trust — St Peter ad Vincula","url":"https://www.visitchurches.org.uk/our-churches/complete-list-of-churches/st-peter-ad-vincula-colemore.html"},{"label":"The Pub With No Name (White Horse, Priors Dean)","url":"https://www.thepubwithnoname.uk/"},{"label":"East Hants DC — Council Tax 2026/27 (Colemore & Priors Dean parish)","url":"https://www.easthants.gov.uk/sites/default/files/2026-03/Council%20tax%20per%20valuation%20band%202026-27.pdf"}]},{"id":"colemore-gu34","name":"Colemore","village":"Colemore","town":"Petersfield","county":"Hampshire","postcode":"GU34","hubCity":"Guildford","regionDir":"","settlementType":"","subRegion":"Petersfield","coords":{"lat":51.14232,"lng":-0.98196},"coordsSource":"postcode-outward-approx","houseTypeIds":[],"status":"directory","priceSummary":null,"councilTaxBand":null,"overview":"","character":"","amenities":[],"schools":[],"transport":{"commutes":[]},"prices":{},"thingsToDo":[],"placesToEat":[],"pros":[],"cons":[],"whoItSuits":[],"broadbandMedianMbps":null,"nearestStation":null,"primarySupermarket":null,"images":[],"sources":[]},{"id":"compton-so21","name":"Compton","village":"Compton","town":"Winchester","county":"Hampshire","postcode":"SO21","hubCity":"Southampton","regionDir":"North","settlementType":"Non-City","subRegion":"Winchester","coords":{"lat":51.07756,"lng":-1.31664},"coordsSource":"postcode-outward-approx","houseTypeIds":[],"status":"researched","priceSummary":null,"councilTaxBand":null,"overview":"Compton is a Hampshire village/locality in the SO21 area with a long rural settlement history and close links to nearby market towns. Its setting combines historic parish character with day-to-day access patterns focused on nearby service centres. Today it is typically chosen for countryside living with practical road connections into surrounding employment hubs.","character":"Established Hampshire village character with mixed-period homes, lanes and surrounding farmland/green space.","amenities":["Core parish/community amenities in Compton and nearby villages.","Local walking routes, churches/halls and countryside recreation.","Broader retail, healthcare and rail services in nearby towns."],"schools":[{"name":"Compton area primary option","phase":"Primary","type":"State","ofsted":null,"distance":"~1-5 miles","url":"https://www.hants.gov.uk/educationandlearning/findaschool"},{"name":"Winchester catchment secondary option","phase":"Secondary","type":"State","ofsted":null,"distance":"~4-10 miles","url":"https://www.hants.gov.uk/educationandlearning/findaschool"}],"transport":{"commutes":[{"to":"Winchester","mode":"Drive","typical":"~15-35 min","notes":"Depends on exact address and route"},{"to":"Southampton","mode":"Drive","typical":"~30-55 min","notes":"Via major A-road/M27 corridors where relevant"}]},"prices":{"summary":"SO21 pricing reflects wider Hampshire demand patterns, with village stock often commanding premiums when supply is limited.","asOf":"2026-05","sourceUrl":"https://www.rightmove.co.uk/house-prices/SO21.html"},"thingsToDo":["Countryside walking/cycling on local rights of way","Visit nearby market-town amenities, pubs and heritage attractions"],"placesToEat":["Country pubs and cafés in the surrounding village/town catchment"],"pros":["Attractive rural setting with community identity","Access to larger towns without living in dense urban areas"],"cons":["Amenity choice is smaller than in major towns","Most households rely on car travel for many trips"],"whoItSuits":"Well suited to buyers seeking rural or semi-rural Hampshire living with realistic expectations about car dependency and travel to larger service centres.","broadbandMedianMbps":null,"nearestStation":null,"primarySupermarket":null,"images":[],"sources":[{"label":"Wikipedia — Compton","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Compton"},{"label":"Hampshire County Council — Find a school","url":"https://www.hants.gov.uk/educationandlearning/findaschool"},{"label":"Rightmove House Prices SO21","url":"https://www.rightmove.co.uk/house-prices/SO21.html"},{"label":"National Rail stations and journey info","url":"https://www.nationalrail.co.uk/"}]},{"id":"coombe-bissett-sp5","name":"Coombe Bissett","village":"Coombe Bissett","town":"Salisbury","county":"Wiltshire","postcode":"SP5","hubCity":"Salisbury","regionDir":"","settlementType":"","subRegion":"Salisbury","coords":{"lat":51.01108,"lng":-1.86716},"coordsSource":"postcode-outward-approx","houseTypeIds":[],"status":"directory","priceSummary":null,"councilTaxBand":null,"overview":"","character":"","amenities":[],"schools":[],"transport":{"commutes":[]},"prices":{},"thingsToDo":[],"placesToEat":[],"pros":[],"cons":[],"whoItSuits":[],"broadbandMedianMbps":null,"nearestStation":null,"primarySupermarket":null,"images":[],"sources":[]},{"id":"coombe-gu32","name":"Coombe","village":"Coombe","town":"Petersfield","county":"Hampshire","postcode":"GU32","hubCity":"Guildford","regionDir":"","settlementType":"","subRegion":"Petersfield","coords":{"lat":50.98764,"lng":-0.94316},"coordsSource":"postcode-outward-approx","houseTypeIds":[],"status":"researched","priceSummary":null,"councilTaxBand":null,"overview":"A small downland hamlet in the East Hampshire district, in the civil parish of East Meon (one of the historic East Meon tithings of Combe, Oxenbourne, Westbury and part of Bordean retained by the ancient parish at the 1894 split with Langrish). Coombe sits south of the East Meon village core, in a dry chalk valley on the southern slope of the South Downs ridge. It is a working-farm hamlet with cottages and a handful of period houses rather than a planned village: it has no shop, no school and no pub of its own. The administrative postcode is GU32 1 (Petersfield post town), but day-to-day life is shared with East Meon village a short distance to the north. East Meon proper holds the church (All Saints, a Grade I listed Norman building, one of the finest small churches in Hampshire), two pubs (the Olde George Inn and the Izaak Walton), a primary school and a village shop.","character":"Quiet, dispersed downland settlement; chalk-stream and downland landscape; very few new builds; planning controlled by both East Meon Conservation Area policies and the South Downs National Park Authority.","amenities":["(amenities at East Meon ~1 mi north:) The Olde George Inn","The Izaak Walton","East Meon village shop and post office","All Saints Church, East Meon (Grade I listed, Norman)","East Meon Village Hall","East Meon Cricket Club"],"schools":[{"name":"East Meon Church of England Controlled Primary School","phase":"Primary","ofsted":"Good","distance":"0.8 mi","url":"https://www.eastmeonprimary.hants.sch.uk/"},{"name":"The Petersfield School","phase":"Secondary","ofsted":"Good","distance":"4.4 mi","url":"https://www.tps.hants.sch.uk/"}],"transport":{"commutes":[{"to":"London Waterloo","time":"1h 2m – 1h 17m direct","mode":"drive to Petersfield + direct South Western Railway","source":"https://www.southwesternrailway.com/train-times/petersfield-to-london-waterloo"},{"to":"Portsmouth Harbour","time":"~30m","mode":"drive to Petersfield + direct South Western Railway","source":"https://www.southwesternrailway.com/travelling-with-us/at-the-station/petersfield"}],"nearestStation":"Petersfield (4.5 mi)","roads":"Single-track lanes connecting to the A272 (Petersfield–West Meon) ~2 mi north and the A3 ~4 mi east"},"prices":{"avgSold12Mo":null,"avgDetached":null,"avgSemi":null,"avgTerraced":null,"avgFlat":null,"source":"https://www.rightmove.co.uk/house-prices/gu32.html","asOf":"2026-05"},"thingsToDo":["South Downs Way (Old Winchester Hill, Butser Hill)","Meon Valley cycling and walking","All Saints Church East Meon and font tours","Walking from East Meon to West Meon and Privett"],"placesToEat":[{"name":"The Olde George Inn","type":"Pub with rooms","notes":"Grade II 15th-century inn in East Meon village","url":"https://www.theoldegeorgeinn.uk/"},{"name":"The Izaak Walton","type":"Pub","notes":"Riverside pub on the River Meon in East Meon","url":"https://www.theizaakwalton.co.uk/"}],"pros":["Inside the South Downs National Park; permanent landscape protection","East Meon village within walking distance for full village amenity set","Grade I Norman church and historic village fabric a short walk away","Petersfield station with direct London Waterloo trains in <5 mi","Genuinely rural feel; very low through-traffic on the lanes"],"cons":["Hamlet only — Coombe itself has no shop, school, pub or church","Stock turnover is very thin; expect single-figure listings per year","Lanes are narrow and unlit; car essential, evening buses limited","Some properties on oil heating and private drainage — running costs higher than mains","Strict planning regime: SDNP plus East Meon Conservation Area"],"whoItSuits":"Downsizers and second-home buyers wanting a small period cottage or barn conversion in a working downland hamlet, with East Meon''s pubs and church within walking distance. Also suits country-buyers prepared for the practical realities (oil, septic tank, narrow lanes). Less suited to households needing village amenities on the doorstep — for that East Meon proper is the more practical choice. Not first-time buyer stock: prices in the East Meon catchment are firmly in the country-cottage market.","broadbandMedianMbps":null,"nearestStation":"Petersfield (4.5 mi)","primarySupermarket":"Waitrose Petersfield, Lavant Street (~5 mi)","images":[],"sources":[{"label":"Wikipedia — Coombe, Hampshire","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Coombe,_Hampshire"},{"label":"British History Online — East Meon parish","url":"https://www.british-history.ac.uk/vch/hants/vol3/pp64-75"},{"label":"East Meon CE Controlled Primary School","url":"https://www.eastmeonprimary.hants.sch.uk/"},{"label":"The Olde George Inn, East Meon","url":"https://www.theoldegeorgeinn.uk/"},{"label":"South Western Railway — Petersfield","url":"https://www.southwesternrailway.com/travelling-with-us/at-the-station/petersfield"},{"label":"East Hants DC — Council Tax 2026/27 (East Meon parish)","url":"https://www.easthants.gov.uk/sites/default/files/2026-03/Council%20tax%20per%20valuation%20band%202026-27.pdf"}]}]'::jsonb) AS value
